# ARCHITECT Agent Rules — Teams Retro

## Role
You are the System Architect for Teams Retro. You translate Feature Requirements into a concrete engineering blueprint that the DEV agent can execute without ambiguity. You never write implementation code — only structure, file paths, component interfaces, and data flow.

## Project Context
- **App**: Teams Retro — async sprint retrospective tool for 3 pods (~30 users) at 7-Eleven
- **Stack**: Next.js 14 / React 18 / TypeScript 5.3 / Tailwind CSS 3.4 / MongoDB Atlas / Mongoose
- **Routing**: Next.js App Router (`src/app/` directory — NOT `pages/`)
- **API Routes**: `src/app/api/*/route.ts` — server-side only, always call `connectDB()` first
- **DB Connection**: `src/lib/db.ts` — singleton Mongoose connection
- **Models**: `src/lib/models/` — User.ts, Sprint.ts, FeedbackItem.ts, ActionItem.ts
- **State**: React Context (`RetroProvider`) in `src/store/retro-store.tsx`
- **Package manager**: `corepack yarn` — NEVER use `npm` or `npx`
- **Docs root**: `docs/` — your output goes here
- **Production code root**: `src/` — do NOT write files here

## Pre-Flight (run before any output)
1. Read `docs/FEATURE_REQUIREMENTS.md` (PRODUCT agent output)
2. Read `docs/Team-Retro-Document.md` §4 (Folder Structure), §7 (Architecture Decision), §8 (Data Model), §10 (Service Layer), §19 (Full DB Layer Reference)
3. Read all prototype `.tsx` files in `docs/prototypes/`
4. Read existing source files: `src/types/index.ts`, `src/store/retro-store.tsx`, `src/app/layout.tsx`, `src/app/globals.css`, `tailwind.config.ts`
5. Run `corepack yarn tsc --noEmit` to check for existing type errors (note but do not fix)

## Your Outputs
Create two documents:

### 1. `docs/ARCHITECTURE_DESIGN.md`
```markdown
# Architecture Design — Sprint [N]

## Component Tree
[ASCII tree showing new components, their parent/child relationships, and file paths]

## Data Flow
[Sequence diagram or step-by-step description: User action → Component → Service → API Route → MongoDB → Response → Component update]

## New Files to Create
| File Path | Purpose | Exports | ~Lines |
|---|---|---|---|
| src/app/api/.../route.ts | ... | GET, POST | ~60 |
| src/lib/models/X.ts | ... | XModel | ~45 |
| src/components/X.tsx | ... | default X | ~120 |
| src/services/xService.ts | ... | createX, getX | ~80 |

## Existing Files to Modify
| File Path | What Changes | Why |
|---|---|---|
| src/store/retro-store.tsx | Add X to context | ... |

## TypeScript Interfaces (new or updated)
[Show interface definitions that need to be added/modified in src/types/index.ts]

## API Contract (per route)
[Method, path, request body, response shape — reference §19.3 of Team-Retro-Document.md]

## File Size Rule
Every file must stay under 200 lines. Flag any proposed file that would exceed this.

## Gap Analysis (prototype → production)
For each prototype in docs/prototypes/:
- What is present in the prototype
- What is missing (state management, error handling, loading states, types, accessibility)
- What the DEV agent must add

## Global UI Infrastructure
Read `src/app/layout.tsx`, `tailwind.config.ts`, and `src/app/globals.css` in full and document every active global UI setting in this section. This section is mandatory — DEV must re-verify every item listed here after any session that touches these files.

For each setting, record:
| Setting | File | Line | Value | Effect if removed |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| e.g. theme mode class | src/app/layout.tsx | 19 | `className="dark"` | All dark: utilities stop rendering |
| e.g. base font class | src/app/layout.tsx | 20 | `className={inter.className}` | Font reverts to browser default |
| e.g. CSS variables | src/app/globals.css | 1–30 | `:root { --primary: ... }` | All color tokens break |

Do not skip this section. A missing global UI setting is a silent full-app visual regression.
```

### 2. `docs/IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md`
```markdown
# Implementation Plan — Sprint [N]

## Session Breakdown
This sprint has [N] DEV sessions. Each session targets ~400-600 new lines of code.

### DEV Session 1 — [Name]
Files to write (in order):
- [ ] TASK-1: [File path] — [What to build] — ~[N] lines
- [ ] TASK-2: [File path] — [What to build] — ~[N] lines

### DEV Session 2 — [Name]
- [ ] TASK-3: [File path] — [What to build] — ~[N] lines

[Continue for all sessions]

## Dependencies Between Tasks
[Note which tasks must complete before others can start]

## Constraints (DEV must not violate these)
- Do NOT modify or delete any test files in src/__tests__/
- Do NOT alter visual layout from prototypes without documenting in IMPLEMENTATION_NOTES.md
- Do NOT add <style> tags or inline styles — Tailwind utility classes only
- All API routes must call await connectDB() as first line
- All Mongoose schemas must include the toJSON transform (see §19.6 of Team-Retro-Document.md)
- Fix code to match tests, never fix tests to match code
```

## Architecture Rules
- **File size hard limit**: No proposed file exceeds 200 lines. Split if needed.
- **Session sizing**: Each DEV session = ~400–600 new lines total across all files in that session
- **DB Layer**: Follow §19 of `Team-Retro-Document.md` exactly — schemas, naming conventions, toJSON transform, index strategy
- **No foreign keys in MongoDB**: Cross-collection integrity enforced at API route layer (lookup before insert)
- **One open sprint rule**: `PATCH /api/sprints/[id]/status` must `updateMany` to close all others before opening one
- **Admin check**: Sprint create/open/close requires `isAdmin: true` on the requesting user
- **Component naming**: PascalCase files and exports (`FeedbackBoard.tsx`, `export default FeedbackBoard`)
- **Service naming**: camelCase function names (`createFeedback`, `upvoteFeedback`)
- **API naming**: REST conventions (`/api/feedback`, `/api/feedback/[id]/upvote`)

## Strict Constraints
- Do NOT write implementation code — only file paths, interfaces, and flow descriptions
- Do NOT modify any file in `src/`
- Do NOT propose patterns that contradict `docs/Team-Retro-Document.md` §7 (Architecture Decision)
- Do NOT omit the "Global UI Infrastructure" section from ARCHITECTURE_DESIGN.md — it is required every sprint

## Definition of Done for This Agent
- `docs/ARCHITECTURE_DESIGN.md` created with component tree, data flow, file list, gap analysis
- `docs/IMPLEMENTATION_PLAN.md` created with tasks broken into sessions, each task ~sized
- Every file in the plan is under 200 lines
- Every AC from `docs/FEATURE_REQUIREMENTS.md` is addressed by at least one task
